begin set xact_abort ON
declare @status int = ( select [id] from [ops].[status] where [status] = 'SUCCEEDED' )
if (@@succeeded != 1) begin set @status = ( select [id] from [ops].[status] where [status] = 'FAILED' ); end
update p set p.[status_id] = @status, p.[started] = getutcdate(), p.[modified] = getutcdate(), p.[modified_by] = suser_sname() from [ops].[process] p join [ops].[status] s on s.[id] = p.[status_id] where p.[id] = @@process_id and s.[status] = 'EXECUTING' end

Property.Name: HeaderContents
Property.Value: create procedure [ops].[get_processes] @@project varchar(150), @@process_group varchar(150) = 'default', @@status varchar(100) = 'WAITING' AS

Property.Name: BodyScript
Property.Value:
begin
set xact_abort on
declare @adf_process_id uniqueidentifier = coalesce(@@adf_process_id, newid()) declare @waiting int = ( select [id] from [ops].[status] where [status] = 'WAITING' ) declare @timeslice datetime = coalesce(@@timeslice, getutcdate())
exec [ops].[save_process] @@project=@@project, @@process_group=@@process_group
if (@@restart = 1) begin update p set p.[adf_process_id] = @@adf_process_id, p.[modified] = getutcdate(), p.[modified_by] = suser_sname() from [ops].[process] p end
if (@@restart = 0) begin
-- if not restarting clear out the current process group run delete p from [ops].[process] p join [metadata].[map] m on p.[map_id] = m.[id] join [metadata].[project] r on m.[project_id] = r.[id] where r.[name] = @@project and m.[process_group] = @@process_group
-- add the new run. insert into [ops].[process]( [map_id], [adf_process_id], [status_id], [timeslice], [parameters] ) select sd.[id], @adf_process_id as [adf_process_id], @waiting as [status_id], @timeslice as [timeslice], @@parameters as [parameters] from [metadata].[source_destination] sd end
end

begin
insert into [ops].[process_history] ( [process_id], [map_id], [adf_process_id], [status_id], [timeslice], [parameters], [started], [finished], [duration_seconds], [created], [modified], [created_by], [modified_by] ) select p.[id], p.[map_id], p.[adf_process_id], p.[status_id], p.[timeslice], p.[parameters], p.[started], p.[finished], p.[duration_seconds], p.[created], p.[modified], p.[created_by], p.[modified_by] from [ops].[process] p join [metadata].[map] m on p.[map_id] = m.[id] join [metadata].[project] r on m.[project_id] = r.[id] where r.[name] = @@project and m.[process_group] = @@process_group
end

begin
select [id], [run_id], [test], [expected], [actual], [executed_at], [result] from [test].[result] where [run_id] = @@run_id;
declare @failed int = ( select count(1) from [test].[result] where result = 'FAILED' and [run_id] = @@run_id )
if (@failed > 0) begin declare @msg varchar(50) = FORMATMESSAGE( '%i or more tests failed.', @failed); throw 60000, @msg, 1; end
end
